'''Lee Sang-Ki''' ([[Hangul]]: <U+C774><U+C0C1><U+AE30>, [[Hanja]]: <U+674E><U+76F8><U+7B95>) (born June 5, 1966) is a [[South Korea]]n foil [[fencing|fencer]].

Lee is a four-time Olympian (1988, 1992, 1996, 2000)<ref name="sports-reference">{{cite web |url=http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/le/lee-sang-gi-1.html |title=Lee Sang-Ki Olympic Results |accessdate=2011-07-25 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref> and bronze medalist at the 1994 World Fencing Championships in [[Athens]], [[Greece]]. At the [[2000 Olympics]] in [[Sydney]], he won the bronze medal in the individual <U+00E9>p<U+00E9>e, defeating [[2004 Olympic Games|2004 Olympic]] champion [[Marcel Fischer]] of [[Switzerland]] in the bronze medal match. 

